% Handwritten A0 — Milestone 1 corpus (refund_handler)
% Each requirement line maps to story ## Covers R1–R5 (see stories/).

<requirements>
Only active users may receive refunds.
The same refund request id must be idempotent: repeating it returns the same outcome.
When the user is unauthorized, reject the refund.
When the refund amount is invalid, reject the refund.
Successful refunds must return a receipt identifier.
</requirements>

<vocabulary>
- active: returns an observable outcome defined by this prompt's rules
- unauthorized: returns an observable outcome defined by this prompt's rules
- invalid: returns an observable outcome defined by this prompt's rules
- successful: returns an observable outcome defined by this prompt's rules
</vocabulary>

<contract_rules>
R1 - Requirement 1
When Only active users may receive refunds
The module MUST satisfy this requirement with an observable outcome.
R2 - Requirement 2
When The same refund request id must be idempotent: repeating it returns the same outcome
The module MUST satisfy this requirement with an observable outcome.
R3 - Requirement 3
When When the user is unauthorized, reject the refund
The module MUST satisfy this requirement with an observable outcome.
R4 - Requirement 4
When When the refund amount is invalid, reject the refund
The module MUST satisfy this requirement with an observable outcome.
R5 - Requirement 5
When Successful refunds must return a receipt identifier
The module MUST satisfy this requirement with an observable outcome.
</contract_rules>

